article.headline: Portland State 63, Jackson State 46
article.story: PORTLAND, Ore. (AP) -- Blake Walker scored 20 points and grabbed 11 rebounds as Portland State defeated Jackson State 63-46 in the Nike Vanport Invitational on Saturday. Sheu Oduniyi added 15 points for the Vikings (3-4) and Seamus Boxley had 10 points and 10 rebounds. K.C. Cavette led the Tigers (1-3) with 13 points while Ishmael Joyce and Leonard Taylor each added eight points. Portland State led the entire game and shot 43 percent as a team from the field. The Tigers struggled offensively all night and shot 29 percent from the field (17-of-58). Portland State also dominated the boards and out-rebounded Jackson State 45-28. The Vikings scored the first eight points of the game and used a 13-1 run midway through the half to build a 25-8 lead with two minutes remaining. Portland State led 27-10 at halftime after holding Jackson State to 4-of-25 from the field. The Tigers would not get closer than 13 points the remainder of the game.
